    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-29T06:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-29T06:29:00-05:00" n="846"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d846">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1531</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vologda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-29T14:00:00+02:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 30, 4.44 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. <persName corresp="#p_RLCR1">Robins</persName> wires following: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs sends me following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>In view of liquidation of the conflict between Russian Soviet
                                    Republic and Rumania, the Minister for Foreign Affairs offered
                                    to the Rumanian Consul General, Moscow, to begin negotiations
                                    for settlement of issues involved in accordance with agreement
                                    made in Odessa and by the mixed commission. In above-mentioned
                                    commission, it was arranged to have representatives of England,
                                    Germany, and the United States.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>The note was handed me without instructions. I forward to you and await
                            your orders.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>This was my first information on the subject. Have you any? <persName
                        corresp="#p_KR1">Kühlmann</persName> has protested to Soviet government
                    against my statement to Russian people that my Government did not recognize
                    separate peace but still considers America ally of the Russian people.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d846fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_440">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                            440</ref>.</note> It was not my intention to please Germany, and I was
                    indifferent concerning effect upon the Russian Government, but thought was
                    reflecting our governmental policy and think no serious complications will
                    eventuate therefrom.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
